    "image_with_text_wKVLmh": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_CLbqn8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Today, Rebellion has two locations, a team of eight barbers, and features a house-made <a href=\"https://www.rebellionbarber.com/goods\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">product line</span></a> sold both in-shop and wholesale. Bodie now spends his time training new barbers, managing product distribution, and staying connected to the clients who’ve been with him from the start. With over a decade of experience, Rebellion continues to be built on craftsmanship, community, and a commitment to helping others grow. We caught up with Michael to hear how he turned a personal hobby into one of Victoria’s most respected barbershops. Read the full interview below.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_CLbqn8"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Screenshot_2025-06-02_at_3_40_05_PM.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "text_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "middle",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 0,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_NjQ3EM": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_ENV8fL": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q:</strong> What are 3 words your friends/family would use to describe you?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Creative, driven, generous.</p><p><strong>Q:</strong> Any advice for someone looking to kick start their entrepreneurial or barbering journey but doesn’t know where to start?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> Imposter syndrome is overblown. Pick any topic or business that you’re considering and spend a couple hours watching videos about it on YouTube. After that you will already know more about it than 99% of the population. If you aren’t interested in that business or hobby after spending a couple hours learning about it then you haven’t wasted much time, so pick a new one! It’s easy to think of a pursuit as something “someone else” does, but everyone doing the thing currently used to not do it.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_ENV8fL"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/image0.jpg",
        "height": "adapt",
        "desktop_image_width": "medium",
        "layout": "image_first",
        "desktop_content_position": "middle",
        "desktop_content_alignment": "left",
        "content_layout": "no-overlap",
        "color_scheme": "scheme-1",
        "mobile_content_alignment": "left",
        "padding_top": 0,
        "padding_bottom": 36
      }
    },
    "image_with_text_FAfVaW": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_tfc8jA": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q:</strong> What are some of your fondest memories since you’ve started your career?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> Some of my fondest memories of my career are based around new opportunities. The first time I got someone to come over for a free haircut, my first day working at a barbershop, when I bought my first professional tools. Probably most significant was when I went out to a bar with my friend who was already in the industry, who helped me a lot, and when someone asked us what we did he said “we’re barbers”. It was the first time I felt like I had an identity. I didn’t know I needed it at the time, but that feeling really propelled me into the field and motivated me to master my craft.</p><p><strong>Q: </strong>What’s the most rewarding part of your job?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> When one of the barbers I trained from scratch has a line of people waiting for them. At this point in my career, the measure of a job well done is the success of the barbers around me. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "text_tfc8jA"
      ],
