    "image_with_text_c4jGUN": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_WTVxJJ": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Q:</strong> If you could give your younger self one piece of advice, what would it be?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Think before you speak and lead with kindness always.</p><p><strong>Q:</strong> What’s your favourite childhood snack?</p><p><strong>A: </strong>Wildberry Pop Tarts.</p><p><strong>Q:</strong> How would you describe your style?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> I’m a retired skateboarder and emo kid, so I would say a grown-up version of that. Unpatterned neutrals, usually dark, and I try to wear stuff that makes me feel good. These days I focus on comfort and shapes. I’m definitely into the big cropped tee and loose-fitting pants. A cropped jacket, tucked in tee with a nice pair of shoes and a belt is another go-to when I don’t want to look like a lazy film director.</p><p><strong>Q: </strong>Any upcoming personal projects you’d like to share with us or a sneak peak?</p><p><strong>A:</strong> I hope to open a third location in the next 18 months. I’m also working on an onboarding handbook for new and experienced barbers looking to join us. </p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        }
      },
